benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/customFields - Add custom fields to account

covered: Valid Payload: TC01 (and related valid payload scenarios TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05) demonstrate successful creation with valid payloads
Invalid Payload: TC08 (malformed JSON), TC09 (empty body), TC27 (partial input missing required fields), TC28 (invalid data types), TC30 (null values handling) cover input validation and error paths
Duplicate Submission: TC12 covers duplicate field names within payload
Large Payloads: TC14 (max payload) and TC15 (payload too large) address payload size boundaries
Validation: TC18 (SQL injection), TC19 (XSS), TC27/TC28 edge cases, TC30/null handling address data validation and security concerns
Server Error Handling: TC16 (unauthorized), TC17 (service unavailable) cover service/auth related errors
Authorization: TC07 (missing CreatedBy header) and TC16 (unauthorized) test authorization behavior
Recovery from transient network failure: TC20 tests retry behavior
Performance tests: TC21 and TC22 cover timing and load aspects for POST
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for POST creation endpoints (not typically applicable for single POST, but could apply to bulk-create patterns)
Rate Limiting: No tests to verify throttling or rate-limiting under high request volume
Caching Behavior: No tests around caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) for POST responses
Internal Server Error (500) scenario: No explicit 500 Internal Server Error test path (only 400/401/403/503 covered)
Duplicate Submissions beyond field-name duplicates: explicit test for repeated identical POST payloads across requests not shown
Explicit 400 vs 201 boundary for some edge cases: ensure consistency across edge-case scenarios (e.g., empty array vs. single-element array)
recommendations: Add a test for bulk-create or multiple-item POST payloads with pagination/rate-limiting considerations if bulk endpoints exist, or confirm bulk behavior is out of scope
Introduce rate-limiting tests to verify throttling under bursty traffic
Add tests around caching headers or absence thereof for POST responses when applicable
Introduce an explicit 500 Internal Server Error scenario to ensure proper server error handling beyond 503
Clarify and add tests for repeated identical POSTs to confirm idempotency or how duplicates are handled across requests
Confirm behavior for edge-case payloads with empty array in a bulk-create context, ensuring consistent error messaging and status codes
